BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:RuBmHpZsotQLTkO73rKn2
SUMMARY:Loose Cannons Improv
DTSTAMP:20260306T011840Z
DTSTART:20260306T040000Z
DESCRIPTION:Thursdays from 8pm - 9:30pm Loose Cannons is Seattle improv at 
	its most unpredictable. Every performance at Unexpected Productions in Pik
	e Place Market is a one-of-a-kind experience: exciting\, unexpected\, a li
	ttle dangerous\, and always ridiculously fun. This is the show where anyth
	ing can happen and usually does. Part One: Part One: The night kicks off w
	ith a unique performance\, setting the performers in a new format with spe
	cial guest improvisers showcasing their signature style or a never-before-
	seen format. Your suggestions fuel the fire\, and the improvisers will ign
	ite the stage\, bringing your ideas to life. Part Two: The second half lau
	nches from a single audience suggestion\, setting the performers in motion
	. It might start with a song\, a monologue\, or a rapid-fire group connect
	ion game. Whatever emerges will inspire spontaneous stories\, surprising t
	wists\, and big comedic swings. Loose Cannons is fueled by audience ideas\
	, fearless performers\, and the thrill of not knowing what hap\n\nhttps://
	www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/loose-cannons-improv-2/?occurrence
	=2026-03-05
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/loose-cannons-improv-2/
	?occurrence=2026-03-05
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:HsPB9kFnXxZvGV4PP94md
SUMMARY:Insider’s Breakfast and Culture Tour of Pike Place Market
DTSTAMP:20260306T011840Z
DTSTART:20260306T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:VOTED 10 BEST FOOD TOURS IN THE COUNTRY BY USA TODAY! Get ahead
	 of peak crowds and join Savor Seattle as they take you behind the scenes 
	on an early-morning exploration of Pike Place Market. Their guides on this
	 tour are deeply rooted members of the Market community who will truly tak
	e you to “Meet The Producer” using their years of experience in the neighb
	orhood. This is an experience you cannot get with any regular tour guide! 
	Feel like a local as you walk and eat your way through the best morning bi
	tes! Learn the names and stories of the people who operate the businesses 
	Seattle Savor's is honored to highlight as their guides give you the full 
	history of how Pike Place became The Soul of Seattle. "Watching the Market
	 come to life is a time-honored Seattle tradition we would love for you to
	 witness as we share our years of expertise with you. Come savor mornings 
	at Pike Place Market!" Tours are available on Monday\, Thursday\, Friday\,
	 Saturday and Sunday from 8am - 10:30pm Book a Tour \n\nhttps://www.pikepl
	acemarket.org/events-calendar/insiders-breakfast-and-culture-tour-of-pike-
	place-market/?occurrence=2026-03-06
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/insiders-breakfast-and-
	culture-tour-of-pike-place-market/?occurrence=2026-03-06
LOCATION:Pike Place Market
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT14H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zbntZULst8s-ltOI_O0g6
SUMMARY:Market to Table Tour & Cooking Class
DTSTAMP:20260306T011840Z
DTSTART:20260306T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:“We wish we did this at the beginning of our trip!” “You’ve exc
	eeded all of our expectations! And then some!!!” … These are some of the f
	requent comments we receive during our Market to Table experience! &nbsp\;
	 Reserve Your Spot! Each experience INCLUDES: • 90-120 minutes VIP TOUR of
	 Pike Place Market\, visiting Chef Traci’s favorite spots\, and includes s
	ome delightful sips and nibbles • 60-90 minute HANDS-ON cooking class (but
	 if you want to sit and watch\, you can do that too!) • 30-60 minute LUNCH
	 or DINNER • All welcome nibbles\, appetizers\, non alcoholic beverages\, 
	tastes & sips along the tour\, all ingredients for a customized cooking cl
	ass • Estimate 3-4 hours for the complete experience • All class menus are
	 created at the start of class and take into consideration individual diet
	ary preferences and allergies (please note: the kitchen is not a gluten-fr
	ee\, nut-free facility\, however menus may be customized to omit nuts\, gl
	uten\, and/or dairy) The Market to Table tour and cooking cla\n\nhttps://w
	ww.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/market-to-table-tour-cooking-class/
	?occurrence=2026-03-06&time=1772789400
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/market-to-table-tour-co
	oking-class/?occurrence=2026-03-06&time=1772789400
LOCATION:Atrium Kitchen\, 93 Pike St\, Seattle\, WA 98101
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:OG7EeNr3xkLyJwaBsZsYt
SUMMARY:The Original Food and Culture Tour of Pike Place Market
DTSTAMP:20260306T011840Z
DTSTART:20260306T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:VOTED 10 BEST FOOD TOURS IN THE COUNTRY BY USA TODAY! Join Savo
	r Seattle for Seattle’s original food and cultural tour of Pike Place Mark
	et! On their signature tour\, they will take you on a journey through the 
	lively and bustling days in the heart of Seattle: Pike Place Market. While
	 their guides give you the most delicious tastings at eight different part
	ners. You’ll also learn the history of the Market and hear the stories of 
	the small-batch food and craft producers that make this place one of Seatt
	le’s most beloved landmarks. Find out why fish fly\, why a pig is our masc
	ot\, how the “Original” Starbucks was founded\, how an alleyway became cov
	ered in gum\, what made Pike Place Market one of Anthony Bourdain’s favori
	te places\, and many more pieces of info Seattle Savor guides we’ll be thr
	illed to share with you while you savor culinary offerings. Once you’re do
	ne\, you’ll be equipped and ready to dive deeper into the historic neighbo
	rhood. Tours are available daily\, starting at 10am and 2\n\nhttps://www.p
	ikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/the-original-food-and-culture-tour-of-p
	ike-place-market/?occurrence=2026-03-06
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/the-original-food-and-c
	ulture-tour-of-pike-place-market/?occurrence=2026-03-06
LOCATION:Pike Place Market
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7f9sG6O9QdGWB0iTzHAgF
SUMMARY:Improv Happy Hour
DTSTAMP:20260306T011840Z
DTSTART:20260306T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Improv Happy Hour—where comedy is unscripted\, unpr
	edictable\, and unbelievably fun! From movie mashups to literary spoofs an
	d bold\, experimental comedy\, our quick-thinking performers turn your sug
	gestions into hilarious scenes on the spot. This family-friendly show at t
	he iconic Gum Wall in Pike Place Market guarantees a night of laughter\, s
	urprises\, and improv magic you won’t forget. Bring your wildest ideas\, y
	our loudest laughs\, and get ready for a one-of-a-kind comedy experience—b
	ecause at Improv Happy Hour\, anything can happen (and usually does)! Buy 
	Tickets\n\nhttps://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/improv-happy-ho
	ur-2/?occurrence=2026-03-06
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/improv-happy-hour-2/?oc
	currence=2026-03-06
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:IPyggvHo3N1O4cJ9r08MG
SUMMARY:Unexpected Productions: Seattle Theatresports Improv
DTSTAMP:20260306T011840Z
DTSTART:20260307T053000Z
DESCRIPTION:Fridays & Saturdays from 9:30pm - 11pm Seattle’s high-energy im
	prov battle where your suggestions shape every scene. Fast\, funny\, unpre
	dictable comedy Fri. & Sat. 9:30 Welcome to Seattle’s funnest improv comed
	y show\, a high-energy\, no-rules showdown where your ideas shape every sc
	ene. Seattle Theatresports at Unexpected Productions’ Market Theater in Pi
	ke Place Market is part comedy battle\, part game night\, and completely p
	owered by the crowd. Boo the judges. Cheer the Gum Wall race and laugh til
	 it hurts! Every show\, two teams of top Seattle improvisers go head to he
	ad\, performing games\, stories\, characters\, and scenes inspired entirel
	y by your suggestions. Judges score the rounds\, decide the winners\, and 
	shape the fun (as we boo them). No scripts. No safety nets. Just fast thin
	king\, bold choices\, and pure creative mayhem. This isn’t your parents’ i
	mprov show\, unless your parents were super cool. Buy Tickets\n\nhttps://w
	ww.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/seattle-theatresports-improv/?occur
	rence=2026-03-06
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/seattle-theatresports-i
	mprov/?occurrence=2026-03-06
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
